cs.GT, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CE 

The paper proposes and analyzes differentially private mechanisms for call auctions, which involves game theory (cs.GT) and privacy (cs.CR). The analysis involves proving bounds and analyzing incentive properties, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also includes simulation results and connections to finance literature, which could fall under computational finance (cs.CE).
